HOUSE BILL 1385
By Harris
SENATE BILL 1417
By Kyle
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 49,
relative to education funding.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-2-609, is amended by designating
the current language as subsection (a) and adding the following as a new subsection:
(b)
(1) A school support organization and a group or organization that
collects and raises money, materials, property, or securities while representing
itself to be a school support organization shall annually provide a detailed report
of the organization's receipts and expenditures while representing itself to be a
school support organization to the department of education by July 1 each year,
unless the school support organization is a booster club, parent teacher
association, parent teacher organization, or parent teacher support association.
(2) The department shall publish a report submitted to the department
pursuant to subdivision (b)(1) for a period of at least three (3) years from the date
by which the report was submitted to the department.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
